{[%evp 0,54,19,31,23,-7,26,38,24,21,5,15,7,14,11,13,28,16,27,13,12,-30,0,33,29,
16,16,-3,-11,-14,42,7,-2,11,15,-1,-1,-45,-34,-70,-61,-157,-150,-185,-156,-162,
-168,-243,-247,-248,-250,-245,-313,-302,-303,-290,-317]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3.
Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 dxc4 5. a4 Bf5 6. e3 e6 7. Bxc4 Bb4 8. O-O Nbd7 9. Qe2 Bg6 10.
e4 ({A familiar and good structure for Black arises after:} 10. Rd1 O-O 11. Bd3
Qe7 12. Bxg6 hxg6 13. e4 e5 14. Bg5 exd4 15. Rxd4 Bc5 16. Rd3 Rfe8) 10... O-O
11. Bd3 Bh5 12. e5 Nd5 13. Nxd5 cxd5 14. Qe3 Be7 15. Ng5 ({After:} 15. Bd2 {
Black uses a typical maneuver:} Nb8 16. Ne1 (16. b4 Nc6 17. b5 Na5 18. Rfc1 Qb6
19. Ng5 Bg6 20. Bxg6 hxg6 21. Bxa5 Qxa5) 16... Bg6 17. f4 Nc6 18. g4 f5 19.
exf6 Bxf6 20. Bc3 Qe8 21. h3 Bd8) ({Whereas:} 15. Ne1 {is met with the
familiar trade:} Bg6 16. f4 Rc8 17. g4 h6 18. Bxg6 fxg6 {[%csl Gg6,Gg7][%cal
Rf8f4]} 19. Nd3 Qb6 20. Bd2 Qb3 21. Rf2 Nb6 {when Black is doing fine.}) 15...
Bxg5 16. Qxg5 Bg6 {[%cal Gc8c4,Gc4e4] Immediately getting rid of the bishop
pair.} 17. Bxg6 ({Or:} 17. Be2 {[%csl Gb8][%cal Gd7b8] When Black should
ideally enter an endgame:} Qxg5 (17... Nb8 18. Qxd8 Rxd8 19. Bd2 Nc6 20. Bc3 f6
21. f4 Be4) 18. Bxg5 Nb8 $1 {When Black does not risk getting checkmated and
has a solid blockading construction on the queenside.} 19. Bd2 Nc6 20. Bc3 Rfc8
21. a5 a6 22. f3 Na7 23. Rfc1 Nb5 24. Bxb5 axb5 25. Bb4 Rc4 26. Rxc4 bxc4 27.
Kf2 f6 {1/2-1/2 (27) Radjabov, T (2710)-Bu,X (2705) Doha 2016}) 17... hxg6 18.
Qg4 Rc8 19. Ra3 Rc4 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gd7e5]} 20. Bg5 Qb6 {[%csl Gd4,Ge5][%cal
Gb6d4,Gd7e5]} 21. Rd1 Nxe5 22. Qh4 f6 23. Rh3 fxg5 24. Qh7+ Kf7 25. dxe5 Ke7
26. Rf3 Rxf3 27. gxf3 Kf7 {0-1 White resigns.} 0-1

