1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 Bg4 5. h3 Bxf3 6. Qxf3 e6 7. Bd3 Nbd7 8. O-O
Bd6 9. Nc3 O-O 10. Rd1 {10.Rd1 has become a bit dusty these days.} Re8 11. Qe2
Qe7 12. Bd2 dxc4 13. Bxc4 e5 {[%csl Gd2][%cal Ge5e4]} 14. dxe5 Qxe5 {[%csl Gh2,
Ge5,Gd6,Rd2][%cal Gb8h2] This is one of the structures to aim when fighting
the enemy bishop pair. White will need a ton of time and patience to live and
see his favourable endgame. But first, he needs to survive the kingside attack,
and this is anything but easy.} 15. g3 b5 16. Bb3 a5 $146 {Not the flashiest
novelty ever.} ({Black's centralization in the following game was far more
impressive:} 16... Nc5 17. Bc2 b4 18. Na4 Nce4 {[%csl Ge4]} 19. Be1 Qe6 $17 20.
Kg2 $2 Ng5 $19 {[%csl Rh3][%cal Re6h3] The knights and the queen prove
enormously strong into the attack.} 21. g4 (21. h4 Qh3+ 22. Kg1 Ng4 {[%csl Rg1]
[%cal Gh3h2,Gh2h1]}) 21... Qe5 {[%csl Gg2][%cal Ge5h2,Gh2g2]} 22. Rxd6 (22. f4
Qxf4) 22... Qxd6 23. Rd1 Qe7 24. Qc4 Nd5 25. Bb3 Qf6 {0-1 (25) Franco Ocampos,
Z (2525)-Felgaer,R (2581) Olite 2006}) 17. Bc2 Qe6 18. Kg2 a4 19. a3 Ne5 20.
Bb1 Qe7 21. Be1 Rad8 22. Ba2 Ned7 23. Qc2 Be5 24. Rac1 ({Missing the nice
tactic:} 24. Nxb5 $3 {[%cal Ge1b4]} cxb5 25. Bb4 {[%csl Re7][%cal Gb4e7]})
24... Nc5 25. Ne2 Rxd1 26. Rxd1 Qa7 27. Rc1 (27. Nd4 $1 $16) 27... Ne6 28. f3
Nd5 29. Qxc6 Nxe3+ 30. Kh1 Qb8 31. Bf2 Bxb2 32. Bxe3 Bxc1 33. Bxc1 (33. Qxc1 $7
$13) 33... Rc8 34. Qe4 Qd6 35. Be3 Qd1+ 36. Ng1 Qc2 37. Qd5 Rd8 {0-1 White
resigns.} 0-1

