Nc3 Nc6 8. f3 $1 {A great new idea by Grischuk, which brings him the full
point in this game. White wants to continue with e4 and take control over the
centre.} Bd7 9. Nxd7 Qxd7 10. e4 e6 11. e5 {Now we reach a "French Structure
and despite the fact that Black manages to exchange his "bad bishop" his
positions remains slighlty worse. Mainly because of the space advantage and
the fact that the f6-knight has no good square to retreat.} Ng8 12. Be3 Bb4 13.
Bd3 Nge7 14. Bf2 Nf5 15. Bc2 Rc8 16. Kf1 Bxc3 {Black is in a hurry to exchange
the knight before White plays Ne2, but now White has a long-term advantage.}
17. bxc3 Na5 18. Rc1 Nc4 19. Qe2 O-O 20. Kg2 f6 21. exf6 Rxf6 22. Bd3 b5 23.
