{This game is significant for the theory of the variation with 4...Bg4. After
this game, I believe that the ball is in White's court to prove something here.
} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 Bg4 5. Ne5 Bf5 6. cxd5 cxd5 7. Nc3 Nc6 8.
f3 g6 $1 {very strong reply!} 9. e4 (9. Bg2 Bg7 10. e4 dxe4 11. fxe4 Be6 12.
Nf3 (12. Nxc6 bxc6) 12... Bg4 13. Be3 O-O 14. O-O Nd7 15. e5 Nb6 $15 {0-1 (51)
Naoum,S (2299)-Kobalia,M (2608) Paleochora 2019}) 9... dxe4 10. Bb5 {This is
White's main idea} Nd7 $1 {another brilliant move which I believe is a fruit
of deep analysys} 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Bxc6 exf3 $1 {Finally the point of White's
idea.} 13. Qxf3 (13. Bxa8 {is the most principle approach, but Black has more
than enough compensation here.} Qxa8 14. O-O Bg4 15. Rf2 Bg7 16. Be3 h5 $13) (
13. O-O Rc8 14. Bxf3 h5 $15 {[%cal Rf8g7,Re8g8]}) 13... Rc8 14. O-O Bg7 15. Be3
O-O 16. Be4 Bxe4 17. Qxe4 Nb6 18. Rad1 Nc4 19. Bc1 e6 20. b3 Nd6 21. Qd3 Nf5
22. Ne2 Qa5 23. g4 Ne7 24. a4 Nc6 25. Ba3 Rfd8 26. Qf3 Rc7 27. Kh1 Qa6 28. Bc5
Qb7 29. Kg2 Rcd7 30. h4 a5 31. h5 Nb4 32. Qxb7 Rxb7 33. g5 Nd5 34. Rd3 gxh5 35.
Ng3 Nb4 36. Rdf3 Bxd4 37. Bxd4 Rxd4 38. Nxh5 Rg4+ 39. Kh3 Rxg5 40. Nf6+ Kh8 41.
Ne4 Rd5 42. Rxf7 Rxf7 43. Rxf7 Rd3+ 44. Kh2 Kg8 45. Ra7 Rxb3 46. Nf6+ Kf8 47.
