{[%evp 0,132,19,31,19,0,23,15,19,-2,4,-14,1,12,49,48,45,45,48,49,38,37,51,22,
50,24,38,15,6,24,13,2,15,-8,2,2,2,-2,2,-3,0,-3,-3,-11,-1,-10,-4,-22,-5,-36,0,3,
-16,-47,-22,-15,-13,-17,-12,-13,-13,-15,-5,-27,-14,-19,-15,-33,-27,-56,0,0,-13,
-2,48,18,37,41,111,35,28,-48,-66,-69,-72,-72,-71,-55,-70,-81,-89,-87,-98,-84,
-75,-110,-114,-195,-210,-219,-220,-354,-348,-360,-259,-263,-241,-376,-415,-423,
-435,-482,-454,-626,-462,-473,-482,-489,-498,-498,-487,-504,-520,-509,-511,
-522,-498,-550,-640,-664,-717,-960,-982,-982,-1038]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3
Nf6 4. g3 Bf5 5. Nc3 e6 6. Nh4 dxc4 7. Nxf5 exf5 8. e3 Nbd7 9. Bxc4 Nb6 10. Bb3
{We reach the same position as in the previous game, but Valentina chooses
another move order now.} Qd7 {Probably this is more accurate because Black
still has a choice between Bd6 and Be7} 11. Qf3 Be7 12. Bd2 g6 {another good
move before casting. Probably Black waits for White to decide where he will
put his king and to castle at the same side.} 13. Rd1 O-O 14. O-O Bb4 {In
Saric's game his opponent prevent this by playing a2-a3} 15. a3 Bxc3 16. Bxc3
Nbd5 17. Bd2 Ne4 $15 {We reach our familiar setup, but with White's pawn on d4.
Now the diagonal a1-h8 is closed, and Black has an advantage. It is a good
example of the light square strategy. All Black's pieces are on the light
squares, and Black's dark-squared bishop is useless.} 18. Bc1 Rfe8 19. Qg2 Nef6
{nice prophylactic against f3 and e4. Now the battle is around that. If White
manages to play e4, then his bishops will be mighty.} 20. Rfe1 Re7 21. Re2 Rae8
22. Rde1 Qc7 23. f3 Qb6 {strong maneuvre, again e4 is not possible.} 24. Ba2 h5
25. Kh1 Qb5 26. Bb1 Qc4 27. Bc2 Nc7 28. Rd1 Ne6 29. Rf2 Nc7 30. Re2 Nb5 31. Bd3
Qb3 32. Bc2 Qd5 33. Bd3 a6 34. Rc2 Qd6 35. Qf2 Nc7 36. Rf1 Ne6 37. Bc4 b5 38.
Ba2 Nc7 39. e4 {finally, White manages to open the position, but Gunina keeps
the position under control and converts it to a full point after some fight.}
fxe4 40. fxe4 Nxe4 41. Qf3 Nd5 42. Bf4 Qf6 43. Be5 Qxf3+ 44. Rxf3 Re6 45. h4
Rd8 46. Re2 f5 47. Kg1 c5 48. Bb1 cxd4 49. Bxd4 Ng5 50. hxg5 Rxe2 51. Ba2 Kf8
52. Rd3 Ke8 53. Kf1 Nf4 54. gxf4 Re4 55. Rc3 Rexd4 56. Rc7 Rxf4+ 57. Ke2 Re4+
58. Kf3 Rd3+ 59. Kf2 Rd6 60. Rc8+ Kd7 61. Ra8 h4 62. Ra7+ Kc8 63. Rg7 h3 64.
Rh7 h2 65. Bb1 Rd2+ 66. Kf3 Re1 0-1

