{[%evp 0,98,19,12,15,12,25,18,15,-17,21,7,49,23,34,20,3,40,42,49,54,32,60,25,
47,-13,50,60,36,-20,-23,-28,5,-47,-31,-31,-26,-18,-18,-18,-35,-31,-24,-30,-43,
-13,-13,-13,78,-8,-16,-24,-24,-27,-23,-23,-24,-56,-36,-90,-98,-96,-50,-65,-42,
-84,-77,-64,-66,-92,-36,15,13,0,2,-53,-42,-62,-66,-66,-56,-70,-58,-67,-53,-131,
-132,-138,-85,-117,-75,-76,-118,-122,-132,-132,-118,-181,-197,-183,-183] This
game is an excellent example how to fight against the f4-c5 bind. Carlsen not
only neutralized White's space advantage with a series of pawn breaks, but he
even managed to eventually create a similar bind himself!} 1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6
3. e3 Bf5 4. c4 c6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Nh4 Bg4 7. Qc2 g6 8. h3 Be6 9. c5 Bg7 10. Bd3
Nbd7 11. f4 {[#] Carlsen shows the proper strategy for Black now:} b6 $1 12. f5
gxf5 13. cxb6 c5 $1 $132 {Dynamic play with the pawns - white pawn center has
evaporated within two moves.} (13... Qxb6 14. Na4 $14) (13... Nxb6 14. Nxf5 $14
) 14. Bxf5 (14. b7 Ra7) 14... Qxb6 15. Na4 Qb5 $1 16. Bd3 (16. dxc5 Qb4+ $19 {
[%cal Gb4h4]}) (16. Nxc5 Nxc5 17. Qxc5 Qxc5 18. dxc5 Ne4 $1 $17) 16... Qb8 $1 {
Another strong queen move that utilizes poor position of white knights.} 17.
O-O (17. Nxc5 Nxc5 18. Qxc5 (18. dxc5 Qb4+ $1 $19) 18... Qg3+ 19. Kf1 Rc8 $1
$19) 17... Qg3 18. Nf5 Bxf5 19. Bxf5 e6 20. Rf3 Qe1+ 21. Rf1 Qg3 22. Rf3 Qh4
23. Rf4 Qh5 24. Bd3 c4 {[#] Suddenly, it is Black who has the central bind!}
25. Be2 Qg6 26. Qxg6 hxg6 27. Nc3 O-O 28. h4 Nh5 29. Rf2 Ng3 30. Bd1 Rab8 31.
Kh2 Nf5 32. Kh3 Nd6 33. g4 f5 34. gxf5 gxf5 {[#] A picturesque position - on
move 11, White had the f4-c5 bind, but Carlsen has completely turned the
tables as he erased white pawn centre thanks to clever dynamic play and
created a mirror image of that bind himself! The backward e3-pawn is very weak
and the world champion eventually broke through white defences.} 35. Rg2 Kh7
36. b3 Rfc8 37. bxc4 Rxc4 38. Ne2 Bh6 39. Bb3 Rc7 40. Bd2 Nf6 41. Rc1 Rxc1 42.
Nxc1 Nde4 43. Nd3 Ng4 44. Re2 Nxd2 45. Rxd2 Bxe3 $19 46. Re2 Rb6 47. Nc5 Kg6
48. Kg3 Kf7 49. Nd7 Rb4 0-1

