preparing c5 next move} 13. Qe2 {sample play} c5 14. Rfd1 Qb6 $11 {A perfect
square for the queen. The opening stage is over and Black has nothing to worry
about. It is hard for White to go for aggressive plans since Bd2 is somewhat
awkwardly placed}) 5... b5 6. Be2 {the latest trend} (6. e5 {is still the most
played move according to the database. However, if Black knows the next couple
of moves his position will be more than fine} Nd5 7. a4 e6 8. Be2 (8. Ng5 Be7
