0-1 (59) Salem,A (2638)-Shankland,S (2662) Sitges 2017} c5 $1 $19) 9... O-O 10.
Ne4 Nd7 11. Bg5 {Trying to trade the dark-squared bishops and get d6 under
control} f6 12. exf6 N7xf6 {Black has created some weaknesses, namely the pawn
on e6 and the e5 square, but in return got rid of the unpleasant White pawn on
e5.} 13. Nxf6+ Bxf6 14. Bxf6 gxf6 $15 {is safe for Black. Denayer, E (2199)
-Michiels, R Charleroi 2001}) (6. a4 {this common idea does not seem to be
