Nd2+ 62. Ke1 b3 63. Nd3 b2 64. Rc5+ Kb6 65. Nxb2 Rxb2 66. Rc8 Ra2 67. Re8 Kb5
68. Rc8 g4 69. Rc1 Ne4 {0-1 Lenderman,A-So,W/Las Vegas 2014/CBMs}) (6. Bb5 e6
7. Nc3 Nge7 $5 8. Rc1 (8. Nf3 a6 9. Be2 (9. Ba4 b5 10. Bc2 Bxc2 11. Qxc2 Rc8
12. O-O Ng6 13. Bg3 Be7) 9... Nc8 $1 {always remember this idea!} (9... Bg4 $1
10. O-O Nf5 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Bxf3 Bd6 $1 13. Bxd6 Nxd6 14. Rc1 O-O $132 15. Na4
Rc8 16. Qb3 Qe7) 10. O-O Bd6 11. Bg3 O-O (11... Bxg3) 12. Rc1 Bxg3 (12... Nb6
$1 {this is also quite playable!} 13. Na4 Nxa4 14. Qxa4 Bxg3 (14... Be7 $5 {
is the suggestion of the computer}) 15. hxg3 Bg4) 13. hxg3 Nd6 $132) 8... a6 $1
9. Be2 (9. Ba4 b5 10. Bc2 Bxc2 11. Qxc2 Rc8 12. Nf3 Ng6 13. Bg3 Bb4 (13... Be7
14. O-O O-O $36) 14. O-O O-O $132) 9... Nc8 $1 {an idea which I like very much!
} (9... f6 10. g4 Bg6 11. Nf3 Bf7 12. Bg3 h5 13. g5 Ng6 14. gxf6 h4 15. fxg7
Bxg7 16. Be5 Ngxe5 17. dxe5 Nxe5 18. Nd4 Rc8 19. O-O Nc6 20. Bg4 Nxd4 21. exd4
Rc6 22. Ne2 h3 23. Rc3 Rh4 24. Rg3 Qc7 25. Re1 Kf8 26. Qd3 e5 27. Qa3+ Qd6 28.
Qxd6+ Rxd6 29. Bxh3 exd4 30. Nc1 Rdh6 31. Bg2 Rxh2 32. Nd3 R2h5 33. f4 Rc6 34.
Bf3 Rhh6 35. Rg2 Rhg6 36. f5 Rh6 37. Nf4 d3 38. Nxd3 Bd4+ 39. Nf2 Rc2 40. Kf1
Rxb2 41. Re2 Rb1+ 42. Re1 Rhb6 43. Nd3 Bc3 44. Rxb1 Rxb1+ 45. Kf2 Ke7 46. Rh2
Kf6 47. Ke3 Kg5 48. Nc5 Rb5 49. Rh7 Bg8 50. Rc7 Kxf5 51. Nxb7 d4+ 52. Kf2 Rb2+
53. Be2 Kf4 54. Nd6 Bd2 55. Kf1 Rb1+ 56. Bd1 d3 {[%emt 0:00:15] 0-1
Harikrishna,P-Firouzja,A/Wijk aan Zee 2021/Mega2021 Update}) 10. Nf3 Bd6 11.
Bxd6 Nxd6 12. O-O O-O 13. Na4 Bg4 $5 (13... Qe7 $132) (13... Rc8 $132) 14. Nc5
Bxf3 15. Bxf3 Qe7 $132) 6... e6 7. Qb3 (7. Nf3 Bd6 $1 {this is more simple and
better!} (7... a6 8. Be2 Nge7 9. O-O Nc8 10. Rc1 Bd6 11. Bxd6 Nxd6 12. Na4 O-O
13. Nc5 Qe7 14. Qa4 Rfc8 15. h3 g5 16. Nd2 Bg6 17. Rc3 Na7 18. Qb3 Rc7 19. Na4
Rxc3 20. bxc3 Rc8 21. Nb6 Rc6 22. c4 dxc4 23. Nbxc4 Nxc4 24. Nxc4 Qc7 25. Ne5
Rc3 26. Qa4 Nc8 27. Qe8+ Kg7 28. Nd7 Qd6 29. Nc5 Qc7 30. Nd7 Qd6 31. Nc5 Qc7
32. Bf3 Nd6 33. Qa8 Rc2 34. a4 a5 35. Nxb7 Nxb7 36. Qxb7 Qxb7 37. Bxb7 Ra2 38.
Bc6 Bc2 39. Rc1 Bxa4 40. Bxa4 Rxa4 41. Rc7 Ra1+ 42. Kh2 Ra2) 8. Bxd6 Qxd6 9.
Rc1 (9. Bd3 Bg4 $1 {lets better try to play for some... imbalances! ..and get
a nice Nd6 against a less good light square bishop!} (9... Bxd3 $11) (9... Nge7
) 10. O-O Nf6 (10... Nge7 11. Rc1 O-O $4 12. Bxh7+ {is something you should
avoid!}) 11. Rc1 O-O 12. h3 Bh5 $1 (12... Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Rac8 14. a3 Na5 15. Qe2
Qe7 (15... a6)) 13. Be2 Bxf3 $1 14. Bxf3 Rfc8 15. Qd2 Qd8 $1 16. a3 (16. Be2
Ne8 17. a3 Nd6 $36) 16... Ne8 17. Rc2 Nd6 18. Be2 Na5 $36)) 7... Bb4 $3 {
This is not common at all here and it leads to very nice positions for Black.
Quite often we take over the initiative! White needs to be very careful.} 8.
Bb5 (8. a3 $6 Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 (9. Qxc3 Rc8 $15 10. Rc1 Nf6 11. f3 O-O 12. Qd2 Qb6
13. b4 Ne7 $3 14. Rc5 (14. Ne2 Rxc1+ 15. Nxc1 Rc8) 14... Nd7) 9... Qb6 $3 {
only White has problems after this!} (9... Qe7 $1 10. Bb5 Nf6 11. Nf3 Rc8 12.
O-O O-O $36) 10. Qxb6 (10. Bb5 Nf6 $17 11. Nf3 O-O 12. Nd2 (12. O-O $4 Bd3)
12... Ne4 $17 (12... Rfc8 $17)) 10... axb6 11. Nf3 Nf6 12. Nd2 O-O 13. Bb5 $2 (
13. Be2 Ra7 $1 $15 14. f3 Rfa8) 13... Rfc8 14. Ke2 Na7 $17 15. Bd3 Rxc3) (8.
